description: Dataset containing information about various computer systems, including their hardware specifications, software details, and inventory information.

metadata.description: Unique hash for internal use.
Internal identifier for the device.
Identifier for the device model.
Identifier for the device product.
Identifier for the device manufacturer.
Identifier for the device family.
Identifier for the device lifecycle.
Identifier for the device taxonomy.
Identifier for the device platform.
Identifier for the device operating system release.
Identifier for the device operating system product.
Name of the device manufacturer, providing human-readable identification.
Name of the device product, providing human-readable identification.
Name of the device model, providing human-readable identification.
Name of the manufacturer of the evidence associated with the device, providing human-readable identification.
Name of the model of the evidence associated with the device, providing human-readable identification.
Identifier for the business unit responsible for the device.
Identifier for the cost center responsible for the device.
Identifier for the location of the device.
Identifier for the chassis type of the device.
Represents the domain or category of the device, providing context for its use and purpose.
Represents the total storage capacity of the device's hard disk drive(s).
Identifies the agent responsible for managing the device's inventory.
A boolean flag indicating whether the device should be ignored or not.
The date when the device was added to the inventory.
Represents the user who last logged into the device.
The name of the device, providing a human-readable label for identification.
Unique identifier for the device, allowing tracking and management of individual devices.
Represents the total memory capacity of the device.
Represents the user account calculated by the device, providing information about the device's user-facing capabilities.
Represents the service pack or version of the device's software.
The date and time when the device was created or manufactured.
The date and time when the device was last updated or modified.
Represents the label or name of the device's platform.
Represents the type of the device's platform, such as operating system or firmware.
Represents the number of hard disk drives (HDDs) in the device.
Represents the number of display adapters in the device.
Represents the name of the device's processor.
Represents the number of processors in the device.
Represents the maximum clock speed of the device's processor.
Represents the total number of physical cores in the device.
Represents the total number of logical cores in the device, which is the number of virtual cores that can be used by the operating system.
